A huge explosion in a dynamite factory on Monday killed at least three people in Greece, according to state media. The explosion took place in a factory in the Itea area of the northwestern town of Gravena in the morning, said Greek public broadcaster ERT. At least three people, including the factoryâ€™s co-owner, died and one got injured. According to West Macedonia Governor Georgios Kasapidis, the explosion was felt in many neighboring municipalities, including Kozani and Gravena. Speaking to state news agency AMNA, a fire service official on the scene said the facility had been reduced to rubble.